    "rich_text_read_button_9BUNLa": {
      "type": "rich-text-read-button",
      "blocks": {
        "text_yBbdj7": {
          "type": "text",
          "settings": {
            "text": "<h2>Caster Wheels & Casters Engineered for Real-World Performance</h2><p>Casters play a critical role in how furniture, equipment, and industrial systems move, stabilize, and perform over time. At Holkie, we design and manufacture caster wheels that deliver smooth mobility, dependable load support, and long-term durability across a wide range of applications.</p><p>With decades of caster engineering experience behind every product, Holkie casters are built to meet the practical demands of workshops, warehouses, offices, retail environments, and custom projects. Whether you need compact furniture casters or heavy-duty industrial casters, our solutions are designed to roll smoothly, lock securely, and perform consistently in real-world conditions.</p><h3>Explore Holkie Caster Types & Mounting Options</h3><p>Different applications require different caster configurations. Holkie offers a complete range of casters and caster wheels, covering multiple mounting styles, wheel materials, and mobility functions.</p><p>Our caster collections include:</p><ul><li>Stem casters for furniture, carts, and light-duty equipment</li><li>Plate casters for stable mounting on workbenches and industrial frames</li><li>Swivel casters for maximum maneuverability in tight spaces</li><li>Locking casters to secure equipment safely when stationary</li><li>Heavy-duty casters designed for high load capacities</li><li>Industrial casters for factories, warehouses, and material handling</li><li>Office chair wheels for smooth rolling and floor protection</li><li>Furniture casters for cabinets, sofas, tables, and storage units</li><li>Workbench casters for mobile workstations and tool benches</li><li>Retractable casters that allow equipment to remain level when not in motion</li><li>Leveling casters that combine mobility with adjustable height control</li></ul><p>Each caster category is engineered to balance strength, movement control, and mounting compatibility.</p><h3>Caster Wheels for Industrial, Commercial & Everyday Use</h3><p>Holkie caster wheels are used across a wide range of environments where mobility, stability, and safety matter:</p><ul><li>Mobile workbenches and tool carts</li><li>Industrial trolleys, racks, and machinery</li><li>Office chairs and adjustable furniture</li><li>Retail displays and store fixtures</li><li>Warehouse equipment and logistics systems</li><li>DIY projects, custom furniture, and maker builds</li></ul><p>By choosing the right caster wheels, businesses and individuals can improve efficiency, reduce physical strain, and extend the lifespan of their equipment.</p><h3>How to Choose the Right Casters for Your Application</h3><p>Selecting the correct casters depends on several practical factors. When evaluating caster wheels, consider:</p><ul><li>Load capacity: Total weight of the equipment plus safety margin</li><li>Wheel material: Polyurethane, thermoplastic rubber, polypropylene, or steel for different surfaces</li><li>Mounting type: Stem, threaded stem, or top plate installation</li><li>Mobility needs: Swivel, rigid, locking, or retractable functionality</li><li>Surface conditions: Smooth floors, concrete, carpet, or uneven ground</li></ul><p>Understanding these factors helps ensure stable movement, reliable braking, and long-term performance.</p><h3>Designed for Flexible Orders & Scalable Projects</h3><p>Holkie casters are trusted by individual buyers, small businesses, and B2B customers worldwide. Our caster solutions support:</p><ul><li>Small-batch orders for repairs, upgrades, or DIY projects</li><li>Scalable sourcing for furniture makers and manufacturers</li><li>Long-term supply for industrial and commercial operations</li></ul><p>From furniture casters to industrial-grade mobility solutions, Holkie provides caster wheels that adapt to changing needs without compromising quality or performance.</p>",
            "enable_read_more": true,
            "read_more_label": "Read More",
            "read_less_label": "Read Less",
            "text_font": "body",
            "text_size": "subtext-sm",
            "text_max_size": 32,
            "text_line_height": 1.6,
            "text_letter_spacing": 0,
            "text_capitalize": false,
            "secondary_color": false,
            "highlighted_text": "none",
            "highlighted_scribble": "circle"
          }
        }
      },
