    "faq_r9UUX4": {
      "type": "faq",
      "blocks": {
        "question_mPjzgx": {
          "type": "question",
          "settings": {
            "title": "What are casters used for?",
            "text": "<p>Casters are used to add mobility to furniture, equipment, and industrial systems. They are commonly installed on workbenches, carts, office chairs, storage units, and machinery to make items easier to move, reposition, and secure safely.</p>",
            "highlighted_text": "none",
            "highlighted_scribble": "circle"
          }
        },
        "question_6mhTHq": {
          "type": "question",
          "settings": {
            "title": "What is the difference between casters and caster wheels?",
            "text": "<p>A caster typically includes the wheel, mounting structure, and swivel or locking mechanism, while a caster wheel refers only to the rolling wheel itself. Complete casters provide both mobility and mounting support for equipment and furniture.</p>",
            "highlighted_text": "none",
            "highlighted_scribble": "circle"
          }
        },
        "question_G4fxdY": {
          "type": "question",
          "settings": {
            "title": "How do I choose the right casters for my application?",
            "text": "<p>Choosing the right casters depends on load capacity, wheel material, mounting type, and how the equipment will be used. Floor surface, required maneuverability, and whether locking or leveling is needed are also important factors to consider.</p>",
            "highlighted_text": "none",
            "highlighted_scribble": "circle"
          }
        },
        "question_eTHVV4": {
          "type": "question",
          "settings": {
            "title": "What are retractable casters used for?",
            "text": "<p>Retractable casters allow equipment to be mobile when needed and rest firmly on the floor when not in motion. They are commonly used on workbenches, machinery, and heavy furniture where stability is required during operation.</p>",
            "highlighted_text": "none",
            "highlighted_scribble": "circle"
          }
        },
        "question_z3nJGM": {
          "type": "question",
          "settings": {
            "title": "What are leveling casters?",
            "text": "<p>Leveling casters combine a rolling wheel with an adjustable leveling foot. After positioning the equipment, the foot can be lowered to stabilize and level it, making leveling casters ideal for uneven floors and precision workstations.</p>",
            "highlighted_text": "none",
            "highlighted_scribble": "circle"
          }
        }
      },
      "block_order": [
        "question_mPjzgx",
